Getting Started
Access the Application
Simply visit: https://drkimogad.github.io/Pet-Health-Tracker/

Authentication
Google Sign-In Only: Securely access your data using your Google account

One-click authentication for seamless access

Automatic data synchronization across your devices

Adding Pets
Click "Add New Pet Profile"

Fill in all pet details

Upload a photo (optional)

Set important reminders

Click "Save Profile"

Managing Profiles
Edit: Click any profile's edit button to modify information

Share: Use the share button for mobile-native sharing or desktop copy options

QR Code: Generate emergency QR codes containing vital health information

Reminders System
Color-coded reminder system:

üî¥ Red: Overdue reminders

üü° Yellow: Due today

üü¢ Green: Upcoming reminders (within 3 days)

One-click deletion of completed reminders

Technical Information
Secure Authentication: Google OAuth 2.0 implementation

Data Storage: Firestore database with local caching for offline access

Image Storage: Secure Cloudinary integration with automatic optimization

Responsive Design: Works seamlessly on mobile, tablet, and desktop devices

Print Optimization: Clean, professional formatting for physical records

Support & Troubleshooting
Common Issues
Authentication Problems: Ensure third-party cookies are enabled in your browser

Data Not Syncing: Check your internet connection and refresh the page

Blank Screen: Enable JavaScript in your browser settings

Getting Help
For technical support or questions about the application:

Email: dr_kimogad@yahoo.com, Petkit2023@gmail.com

Please include a description of your issue and any error messages you're seeing

Privacy & Security
Your data is stored securely and only accessible through your Google account

Photos are processed and stored securely with encryption

No personal data is shared with third parties without your explicit consent

